<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-09-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-09-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="1316" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1316">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 711.13/34.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">American Minister to Coata Rica</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-09-20">
                                    <hi rend="italic">September 20, 1913</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>In regard to Salvador’s invitation reported in your September 19, you may
                            if opportune suggest to Costa Rica that its acceptance should be based
                            upon the willingness of Nicaragua to attend such a conference rather
                            than merely on the extending of an invitation to Nicaragua.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>